description:
RfPort: Table containing RF port information for various cells in a radio access network.

- dateTime: Timestamp of the data record.
- Area_Name: Geographic area where the cell is located.
- CellId: Unique identifier of the cell site.
- Id2: Redundant cell identifier (appears to be identical to CellId).
- Id3: Secondary identifier for the RF port.
- Id4: Tertiary identifier for the RF port (likely representing a port type or designation).
- vsDataType: Data type identifier.
- vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format.
- RfPort.userLabel: User-defined label for the RF port.
- RfPort.pimdAlarmActive: Status of PIMD (Passive Intermodulation Distortion) alarm.
- RfPort.vswrSupervisionActive: Status of VSWR (Voltage Standing Wave Ratio) monitoring.
- RfPort.rfPortId: Identifier for the RF port within the cell site.
- RfPort.nodeUniqueRfPortId: Unique identifier for the RF port across the network.
- RfPort.pimdMeasDuration: Duration of PIMD measurement.
- RfPort.pimdThreshold: Threshold for PIMD alarm triggering.
- RfPort.rlFreqSweepFailedReason: Reason for failure of radio link frequency sweep.
- RfPort.dlFrequencyRanges: Downlink frequency ranges used by the RF port.
- RfPort.antennaSupervisionActive: Status of antenna monitoring.
- RfPort.microSleepTxRadioCapability: Capability of the RF port for micro-sleep transmission.
- RfPort.ulFrequencyRanges: Uplink frequency ranges used by the RF port.
- RfPort.microSleepTxRadioStatus: Current status of micro-sleep transmission.
- RfPort.administrativeState: Administrative state of the RF port (locked/unlocked).
- RfPort.rlFreqSweepStatus: Status of radio link frequency sweep.
- RfPort.automaticANUrecovery: Status of automatic ANU (Automatic Network Update) recovery.
- RfPort.availabilityStatus: Availability status of the RF port.
- RfPort.operationalState: Operational state of the RF port (enabled/disabled).
- RfPort.vswrSupervisionSensitivity: Sensitivity level for VSWR monitoring.
